name: Will to Live Lotus Rebirth by Daniel Kordan

metadata.name: Lotus rebirth #1
metadata.description: The lotus flower holds great symbolic weight in many Eastern cultures and is considered one of the most sacred plants in the world. With lotus roots latched in mud, it submerges every night into river water and miraculously re-blooms the next morning, sparklingly clean. In many cultures, this process associates the flower with rebirth and spiritual enlightenment.
